ENGR 3191-3196 - Engineering Co-Op I - VI
First (For ENGR 3191 and second, third, fourth, fifth, sixth for ENGR
3192-3196, respectively) engineering cooperative education work
experience. Full-time engineering position for length of the academic
term. Requirements include submission of educational objectives for the
work term, biweekly status reports, and a final technical report. In
collaboration with the employer, the student hosts a work site visit by the
instructor and submits at the end of the work term a performance
appraisal/evaluation by the employer.
Prerequisite: Approval for participation in Engineering Cooperative
Education. Graded on a credit/no credit basis.
